A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 13, 2025, as World Refugee Day at the state capitol; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Georgia has a long history of extending welcome to new Americans from
4 around the world, giving them an opportunity to live, work, and thrive in the state; and
5 WHEREAS, today, one in ten Georgians—more than one million people—are foreign-born,
6 bringing valuable skills and talents from countries around the world to the state; and
7 WHEREAS, approximately one in eight Georgia workers is foreign-born, as are one in five
8 doctors and home health aides; one in five science and technology professionals; one in five
9 manufacturing workers; and nearly half of all workers in the construction industry; and
10 WHEREAS, hardworking foreign-born Georgians across all sectors paid over $11 billion in
11 federal, state, and local taxes and held more than $32 billion in spending power in 2021
12 alone; and
13 WHEREAS, nearly half of all foreign-born Georgians are already naturalized United States
14 citizens eligible to vote and many more are on the path toward citizenship; and
